Here’s How To Style Your Outfits This Fall…. instead of just wearing them ! 💾SAVE THIS FOR YOUR FALL STYLING REFERENCE! 

Tip 1: Fall weather can be unpredictable, so layering is key. Start with a base layer like a lightweight top or long-sleeve shirt, add a mid-layer like a cardigan or flannel shirt, and top it off with a versatile trench that you can easily remove if it warms up.

Tip 2: Embrace the warm and cozy colors of fall by incorporating earthy tones into your wardrobe. Think shades like rust, olive green, mustard yellow, and deep burgundy. These colors complement the autumn landscape and create a seasonal look.

Tip 3: Play with different textures to add depth to your outfits. Consider items like leather boots,  loafers, and knit scarves. Don’t forget to accessorize with pieces like statement belts, cozy gloves, and stylish faux fur handbags to complete your fall look.
